<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-03-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-03-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="1056" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1056">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/14735.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Adjutant General</gloss> to
                                General <persName type="to">Funston</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">War Department</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-03-29">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 29, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>American Consul Matamoros on March 27 telegraphed State Department that
                            there had been some firing from Brownsville, Texas, into Matamoros,
                            Mexico. Secretary State has requested Governor Texas to have local
                            authorities take appropriate precautionary measures to prevent
                            repetition. He requests United States military authorities <pb facs="0913" n="797" xml:id="pg_797"/> in vicinity Brownsville be
                            instructed by wire to the end that further firing from Brownsville into
                            Matamoros be prevented. Take appropriate measures accordingly.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">McCain.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>